    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nAlthough URIs are not exclusively for `net`(work) specific applications, `vim.net` is a fitting module to put `uri_encode`, `uri_decode`, `uri_from_fname`, `uri_to_fname`, `uri_from_bufnr`, and `uri_to_bufnr`. Would also clean-up 6 of 67 public functions in the `vim` namespace.\n\nDownside: Another deprecate cycle. Not sure if it's worth it.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n- `vim.uri_decode` -> `vim.net.uri_decode`\n- `vim.uri_encode` -> `vim.net.uri_encode`\n- `vim.uri_from_fname` -> `vim.net.uri_from_fname`\n- `vim.uri_to_fname` -> `vim.net.uri_to_fname`\n- `vim.uri_from_bufnr` -> `vim.net.uri_from_bufnr`\n- `vim.uri_to_bufnr` -> `vim.net.uri_to_bufnr`",
